{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSFileDatabaseRef\/verify(chain:purpose:identity:interaction:flags:cancellable:)-4p7zn","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Determines the validity of a certificate chain, outside the context"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of a TLS session."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"verify"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"TLSCertificateT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"chain","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TLSCertificateT"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"purpose","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"identity","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketConnectableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO20SocketConnectableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnectableRef"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"interaction"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TLSInteractionRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17TLSInteractionRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSInteractionRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"text":"flags","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"TLSDatabaseVerifyFlags","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO22TLSDatabaseVerifyFlagsV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSDatabaseVerifyFlags"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateFlags","text":"TLSCertificateFlags","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO19TLSCertificateFlagsV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TLSCertificateT"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TLSCertificateProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO22TLSCertificateProtocolP"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"chain"},{"text":" is a chain of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificate","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" objects each pointing to the next","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"certificate in the chain by its ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificate","type":"reference"},{"text":" property.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"purpose"},{"type":"text","text":" describes the purpose (or usage) for which the certificate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is being used. Typically ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"purpose"},{"type":"text","text":" will be set to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/tlsDatabasePurposeAuthenticateServer","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"which means that the certificate is being used to authenticate a server"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(and we are acting as the client).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identity"},{"type":"text","text":" is used to ensure the server certificate is valid for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the expected peer identity. If the identity does not match the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"certificate, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"badIdentity"},{"type":"text","text":" will be set in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return value. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identity"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", that bit will never be set in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the return value. The peer identity may also be used to check for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pinned certificates (trust exceptions) in the database. These may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"override the normal verification process on a host-by-host basis.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Currently there are no ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flags"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"none"},{"type":"text","text":" should be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"used."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"chain","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is found to be valid, then the return value will be 0. If","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"chain","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is found to be invalid, then the return value will indicate at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"least one problem found. If the function is unable to determine","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"whether ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"chain"},{"type":"text","text":" is valid (for example, because "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"triggered before it completes) then the return value will be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"genericError"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be set accordingly.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" is not set when "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"chain"},{"text":" is successfully analyzed but found to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be invalid."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GLib guarantees that if certificate verification fails, at least one"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"error will be set in the return value, but it does not guarantee"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that all possible errors will be set. Accordingly, you may not safely"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"decide to ignore any particular type of error. For example, it would","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be incorrect to mask "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"expired"},{"type":"text","text":" if you want to allow"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"expired certificates, because this could potentially be the only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error flag set even if other problems exist with the certificate."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.48, GLib’s default TLS backend modified "},{"code":"chain","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"represent the certification path built by ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSDatabase","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" during","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"certificate verification by adjusting the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificate","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"property of each certificate in ","type":"text"},{"code":"chain","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Since GLib 2.48, this no"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"longer occurs, so you cannot rely on "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificate"},{"text":" to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"represent the actual certification path used during certificate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"verification."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because TLS session context is not used, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSDatabase","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" may not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"perform as many checks on the certificates as "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnection","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" would."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For example, certificate constraints may not be honored, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"revocation checks may not be performed. The best way to verify TLS"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"certificates used by a TLS connection is to let ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnection","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"handle the verification."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The TLS backend may attempt to look up and add missing certificates","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to the chain. This may involve HTTP requests to download missing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"certificates.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This function can block. Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_tls_database_verify_chain_async()"},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"perform the verification operation asynchronously.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tlsfiledatabaseref\/verify(chain:purpose:identity:interaction:flags:cancellable:)-4p7zn"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSFileDatabaseRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSFileDatabaseRef\/TLSDatabaseProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"title":"verify(chain:purpose:identity:interaction:flags:cancellable:)","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GIO","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO19TLSDatabaseProtocolPAAE6verify5chain7purpose8identity11interaction5flags11cancellableAA19TLSCertificateFlagsVqd___SPys4Int8VGSgAA20SocketConnectableRefVSgAA014TLSInteractionP0VSgAA0b6VerifyL0VAA011CancellableP0VSgtKAA0kC0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO18TLSFileDatabaseRefV","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"verify"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"TLSCertificateT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"chain"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"TLSCertificateT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"purpose","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"identity","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text